# Integration Testing for Smart Task Monitoring System

## How to Run Integration Tests

### 1. Set Up Environment
- Java 11+ installed
- MySQL Server running
- Execute `database_setup.sql` before running tests

### 2. Run Integration Tests in IntelliJ/Eclipse
- Open `IntegrationTestSuite.java`
- Run as JUnit test.

### 3. Run from Command Line (If using Maven)

mvn verify

### 4. Test Scenarios
- User authentication and login process
- Task assignment and retrieval from database
- Notifications being triggered when tasks are completed
- Database constraints handling user removal

## Expected Outcome
- The system should pass all integration test cases.
